article.headline: Niagara 75, Manhattan 51
article.story: RIVERDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- J.R. Duffey scored 21 points and Clif Brown had 20 to lead Niagara over Manhattan 67-51 Friday night in a Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference game. The Purple Eagles (8-12, 5-7) trailed 23-15 with 6:55 left in the first half, but took a 27-25 halftime lead. Niagara scored the first nine points of the second half and completed a 48-18 streak when James Mathis hit a jumper with 4:45 left in the game, making the score 63-41. Mathis finished with 17 points and 10 rebounds, while Duffey grabbed 11 boards. Arturo Dubois had 17 points and 11 rebounds for the Jaspers (13-7, 9-3), who fell out of a first-place tie with Iona in the MAAC. Manhattan was held to its lowest point total of the season. The Jaspers lost 66-52 to Seton Hall in their season opener on November 14.
